==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inexplicable
<hw>In*ex"pli*ca*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inexplicabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>inexplicable</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Explicable</er>.]</ety> <def>Not explicable;
not explainable; incapable of being explained, interpreted, or accounted
for; <as>as, an <ex>inexplicable</ex> mystery</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧An
<xex>inexplicable</xex> scratching.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their reason is disturbed; their views become vast and perplexed,
to others <qex>inexplicable</qex>, to themselves uncertain.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inexplicableness</ent>⟦br⟧
